The invention will be discussed below in detail with reference to the accompanying drawings, in which:


FIG. 1 is a lens arrangement of a photographic lens of the embodiment;


FIGS. 2A, 2B, 2C, 2D and 2E show aberration diagrams of the photographic lens when focused at infinity;


FIGS. 3A, 3B, 3C, 3D and 3E show aberration diagrams of the photographic lens when focused at an intermediate distance under the condition that the ratio,  DELTA x2/ DELTA x1, of traveling distances of the front and rear lens group is constant;


FIGS. 4A, 4B, 4C, 4D and 4E show aberration diagrams of the photographic lens when focused at the most close-up distance under the condition that the ratio,  DELTA x2/ DELTA x1, of traveling distances of the front and rear lens group is constant;


FIGS. 5A, 5B, 5C, 5D and 5E show aberration diagrams of the photographic lens when focused at an intermediate distance under the condition that the ratio,  DELTA x2/ DELTA x1, of traveling distances of the front and rear lens group is variable;


FIGS. 6A, 6B, 6C, 6D, and 6E show aberration diagrams of the photographic lens when focused at the most close-up distance under the condition that the ratio,  DELTA x2/ DELTA x1, of traveling distances of the front and rear lens group is variable;


FIG. 7 shows the traveling paths of each lens group of the photographic lens at the time of focusing.
